   1:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c **** /**
   2:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   ******************************************************************************
   3:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   * @file    system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c
   4:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   * @author  MCD Application Team
   5:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   * @brief   CMSIS Cortex-M55 Device Peripheral Access Layer System Source File
   6:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *          to be used after the boot ROM execution in an applicative code called
   7:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *          "FSBL" for First Stage Boot Loader.
   8:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *
   9:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *   This file provides two functions and one global variable to be called from
  10:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *   user application:
  11:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *      - SystemInit(): This function is called at secure startup just after the
  12:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                      boot ROM execution and before branch to secure main program.
  13:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                      This call is made inside the "startup_stm32n6xx_fsbl.s" file.
  14:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                      This function does not manage security isolation (IDAU/SAU,
  15:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                      interrupts, ...) unless USER_TZ_SAU_SETUP is defined at
  16:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                      project level.
  17:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *
  18:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClock variable: Contains the CPU core clock, it can be used
  19:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                                  by the user application to setup the SysTick
  20:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                                  timer or configure other parameters.
  21:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *
  22:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClockUpdate(): Updates the variable SystemCoreClock and must
  23:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                                 be called whenever the core clock is changed
  24:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *                                 during program execution.
  25:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccDjXCr4.s 			page 2


  26:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *   After each device reset the HSI (64 MHz) is used as system clock source.
  27:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *   Then SystemInit() function is called, in "startup_stm32n6xx_fsbl.s" file, to
  28:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *   configure the system before to branch to main program.
  29:Src/system_stm32n6xx_fsbl.c ****   *
